<item>
            <title>[LU-13786] Take server-side locks for direct i/o</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13786</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Trying to investigate an idea that client side locks are not needed for direct i/o, formally, there is no client cache to protect, and client locks are expanded at server to the maximum extent while server-side locks are not (part of lock-ahead patch).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The improvement was initially implemented for Luste-1.8 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=18801&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=18801&lt;/a&gt;) and lost during client re-write (CLIO).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
